[center][size=3][b]Using production queues to produce goods for generating extra credits[/b][/size][/center]
Consider using your production queues for generating extra credits by producing goods. You should time limit the production to one hour intervals by specifying [color=lime]1h[/color] as the quantity. The system will automatically calculate the amount of goods to produce. You can fill up the queue to a maximum of 12 hours. If you have a production capacity of 2200 across all bases, then you will generate an extra 110 credits an hour. The downside to doing this is that you will lose the ability to immediately switch to producing ships if needed.


